After 1.5 years we are reunited. I've been asked a lot of questions about how/why this happened. The nutshell is that he didn't like traveling with me when I was trying to find a new home in Mexico. 

The stress significantly impacted his health. I brought him back to the US, and left him with friends after spending 5 weeks integrating him into their home. 

After, I left for Mexico again, thinking I'd found a new home for us. That ended up not working out for so many reasons, and I was heartbroken. 

I needed a place on US soil that had sunshine and warmth, because I simply could not go back to the Pacific Northwest. 

I pivoted fast and decided to move to Tucson 5 days before Christmas 2021.

But...it was very clear that he was extremely happy where he was.

Truly living his best life, surrounded by love and care.

Long story short, I chose his happiness over my own desire to have him back.

To not stress him out by bringing him on another plane, to another new home, where I hadn't even settled into my own life.

I was heartbroken so many days over that choice. But I knew I had to operate for his well-being, not my ego.

His return this weekend has been several months in the making.

Everything has been thought through in order to make his transition as easy as possible.

I'm behind grateful to @kennylee05
for treating him like her own fur baby. 

It's been such a complex, emotional, bittersweet transition.

He's doing well since arriving, but this is stressful for him...being forced to leave the place and people he's known as his home for so long.

We're taking things slow. 

Send him a little kiss of love for his easeful transition if you feel like it.

New Year's Eve photo dump and some thoughts on being tired and living in beauty:  The general feeling I've noticed a lot of us seem to have is that 2023 left us feeling depleted. It's been that way for me. 

Even last night, while preparing a scrumptious vegan curry for New Year's Eve dinner, I nicked my finger on a tin can😖

That one tiny little cut was such a disaster. It was messy, and slowed me down significantly.

Such a metaphor.

Here we are, nicked, bruised, scraped, bleeding, and pulling into a New Year with renewed sense of hope that January 1 brings.

I pray every day for peace. For the safety of those who are in deep trauma and despair. That they may be blessed as world "leaders" decide their fate. May those in power be persuaded to peace.

I believe that pursuing beauty, love and kindness in ourselves allows us to be better for each other.

Conjuring more beauty in and around us, can add momentum to feeling better - which cascades out into the world.

It’s scientifically proven that there's a circular effect of beauty and goodness.

And in this community I promote being in Beauty, as often as possible, because it's such a powerful path to healing places in the heart the words simply cannot touch.

Wishing you a safe and healthy 2024, filled with moments of incredible beauty!

.
